fragment_downloaded_cb({"url": "gtkdrawingarea-h.html#gtk_drawing_area_set_content_width", "fragment": "Gtk.prototype.set_content_width \nGtk.DrawingArea.set_content_width \ngtk_drawing_area_set_content_width \nSets the desired width of the contents of the drawing area. Note that because widgets may be allocated larger sizes than they requested it is possible that the actual width passed to your draw function is larger than the width set here. You can use Gtk.prototype.set_halign to avoid that. \nIf the width is set to the default the drawing area may disappear. \nParameters \na Gtk.DrawingArea \nthe width of contents \nSince \nSets the desired width of the contents of the drawing area. Note that because widgets may be allocated larger sizes than they requested it is possible that the actual width passed to your draw function is larger than the width set here. You can use Gtk.Widget.set_halign to avoid that. \nIf the width is set to the default the drawing area may disappear. \nParameters \na Gtk.DrawingArea \nthe width of contents \nSince \nSets the desired width of the contents of the drawing area. Note that because widgets may be allocated larger sizes than they requested it is possible that the actual width passed to your draw function is larger than the width set here. You can use gtk_widget_set_halign to avoid that. \nIf the width is set to the default the drawing area may disappear. \nParameters \na GtkDrawingArea \nthe width of contents \nSince \n"});